&quot;Cavehill, historically known as Ben Madigan (from Irish: Beann Mhadagáin), is a basaltic hill overlooking the city of Belfast in Northern Ireland. It forms part of the southeastern border of the Antrim Plateau. It is distinguished by its famous 'Napoleon's Nose',[1] a basaltic outcrop which resembles the profile of the famous emperor Napoleon.&quot;
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cavehill" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cavehill</a>

I'm not sure this view is possible anymore, as there are a lot more buildings and vegetation.  My guess is that this is looking from the Antrim Road.
